## 🟠 Moderate Gaps

### 8. Expand error codes
- **File**: [errors.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/errors.py#L11-L58)
- **Implementation**: [ErrorCode](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/errors.py#11-58) Enum contains all required 1xxx to 9xxx series codes.

### 9. Implement module versioning and rollback
- **File**: [loader.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/loader.py#L34-L43) ([rollback](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/loader.py#34-44))
- **File**: [loader.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/loader.py#L88-L100) ([_check_compatibility](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/loader.py#88-100))
- **Implementation**: Enforces kernel compatibility checks and maintains a `_backups` map for single-version rollback.

### 10. Implement module health checks
- **File**: [loader.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/loader.py#L184-L191)
- **Implementation**: Inspects module namespace for [Module](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/loader.py#17-222) class and executes [initialize](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/interfaces.py#234-237).

### 11. Implement secret rotation and TTL expiry
- **File**: [vault.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/secrets/vault.py#L105-L116) (TTL logic)
- **File**: [vault.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/secrets/vault.py#L160-L172) (Expiry enforcement)
- **Implementation**: [retrieve_secret](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/secrets/vault.py#132-184) raises `ErrorCode.SECRET_EXPIRED` if `expires_at` (derived from TTL) is in the past.

### 12. Implement metering→policy enforcement loop
- **File**: [node.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/metering/node.py#L88-L103)
- **Implementation**: [record](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/interfaces.py#174-177) triggers a policy evaluation; if denied, it publishes a `system.budget_exceeded` event.

### 13. Expand forbidden imports list
- **File**: [main.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/main.py#L107-L123)
- **Implementation**: Precise list of 11 forbidden imports (`os`, [sys](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/main.py#212-222), `subprocess`, etc.) enforced via AST scan in [ModuleLoader](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/module_loader/loader.py#17-222).

